                    </div>
                    <span>I listened to the book on tape, the narration was excellent. What I particularly liked was that this book was about ordinary life in Russia, rather than the political situation. Lots of bleak description on all sorts of aspects of Russian life during the years following the fall of the Soviet Union. Fascinating, very long, and rather depressing.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">makes you appreciate the fact that you don't live in russia</div>
